Vice President Biden issued a statement on the International Day for the Elimination of Violence Against Women, acknowledging the millions of women affected by violence worldwide. He emphasized that violence against women not only harms their safety and dignity but also impacts the health, economic stability, and security of nations. The U.S. government remains committed to promoting women's rights domestically and as part of its foreign policy. Biden joined women and men globally in condemning all forms of violence against women and renewing the commitment to ensuring their freedom from violence and abuse.